The paper deals with deep learning techniques for 3D mesh segmentation, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper proposes a novel convolutional neural network (CNN) architecture and compares it with other deep learning techniques, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of conformal factor (CF) in their technique, which is a mathematical concept that falls under neural networks (cs.NE).
